# Dataset source: https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/Material_composition_of_consumer_electronics/11306792
# License: CC0 (Public Domain)
# Citation: Babbitt et al. (2020) - Disassembly-based bill of materials data for consumer electronic products
#
# Expected test scenarios:
# 1. iPhone family (4, 5, 6, 7) should cluster with high similarity (>0.7)
# 2. Kindle generations should cluster together
# 3. Cross-category (phone vs laptop) should show low similarity (<0.3)
# 4. PlayStation vs Xbox should show medium similarity
#
# To enable these tests:
# 1. Run: python test/scripts/prepare_figshare_data.py --output test/data/figshare/
# 2. Uncomment the test queries below

